1.4.14	On the subject of the time it takes to transfer data to your external.	St
1.4.15	The speed of this is not dependent on your processors.	St
1.4.16	Firewire transfers are dealt with by the firewire controller and really don't involve the processors at all.	St
1.4.17	If you have some form of processor indicator installed, showing real time processor load, you will note that the processor(s) stay down in the single digits during the transfer.	St
1.4.18	This is one of the reasons that Firewire is preferred over USB for transfers.	St
1.4.19	Although USB has a higher stated throughput, it is only attainable in bursts.	St
1.4.20	Firewire supplies a constant stream.	St
1.4.21	Of course, depending on the version of your 1GHz iMac, and if your external is USB, your speed problem would be directly related to the USB 1.1 ports.	St
